Tournament:

A tournament is a competition type in which four or more teams, or many participants, compete in the same sport or game. A single-elimination, knockout, or sudden death tournament is a type of elimination tournament where the loser of each match-up is immediately eliminated from the tournament.

Pyramid:

Pyramid Competition System enables players to challenge each other to a match, the winners move up and the losers move down. The aim is to get to the top of the Pyramid. In a league, individual players or groups of teams in a particular sport compete with each other. Every participant of the league plays at least one game with all the others. Points are collected according to the results. After all games are played, those who collect the most points win.
